#13100
A Cauldron of Guttering Flame~
   The walls and floors of this massive hall have been hewn directly from a
rich bed of basalt so prevalent within the local chain of volcanic mountains.
The floors have been polished to a smooth finish, the mottled greys glinting
lightly in the flickering light.  The walls have been spared such elaborate
treatment, seeming left as they were when first rough hewn, although now
sporting several sconces dancing with torchlight.  A large, bronze cauldron
rests slightly distant from the corner, flames guttering lightly within.    
