#13108
Pillars of Flame~
   The floors here are unadorned unlike the chambers above, hewn of what is
likely a large bed of natural, volcanic basalt.  While unpatterned or styled,
they are well polished and smooth, slightly chill to the touch, particularly
when compared to the surrounding heat of flame and brazier.  Dominating this
chamber is a massive support pillar, soaring upwards to the distant ceiling
nearly shrouded in shadow.  Masterfully crafted and styled of the natural
basalt of the chamber, this column resembles nothing so much as a gigantic
flame reaching up to lick the heights above.  The column itself almost seems
slightly warm to the touch, though whether this is some trick of masonry or
simply the mind is hard to say.    
