Rain of Fire~
   The floors of the chamber are simple and unremarkable, set of the same
polished basalt prevalent within the hall.  A large pool of lava dominates this
area, contained barely within an immense basin of ornate obsidian, fed by a
scalding stream that rains down from the ceiling far above.  The area is left
open, so great care must be taken never to venture too closely to the
incredibly dangerous rain of molten rock and metals.  The pools themselves are
wide enough to contain any splash from the lava's decent and, as one curiousity
to the floor, wide grooves covered in thick, likely magically treated, glass
carries a flow of the molten materials to the chambers to the east, north, and
south.    
