A Wide, Steep Stair~
   A great series of stairs reaches skyward along the southern face of this
imposing structure, and that is where you now find yourself.  The ziggurat
itself has been forged of massive slabs of rough, volcanic basalt, each one of
a size and weight that is staggering to the mind.  Set here amongst the
impressive Lords of Doom, a dangerous and highly active chain of volcanoes, the
temple is continuously awash in light, whether it be that of the blazing sun
above, or the dull, reddish glow of the many lava flows that wind throughout
the surrounding area.    
