A Large, Open Landing~
   This large landing is a welcome change from the steep climb of the many,
many stairs to the top of the ziggurat.  It is left open to the air and
elements, providing a most impressive view of the surrounding landscape,
nessled here amongst the towering peaks of the Lords of Doom.  The surrounding
areas are quite inhabitable, the only notable exception being the nearby city
of Sanction, for the many volcanoes in the region rumble with magma and
continually belch ash and smoke to the air.  Despite the slight haze provided
from the volcanic plumes, the lay of the peaks here allow for full exposure to
sun by the day while the scattered rivers of lava provide a dull, red glow even
by night.    
