A Twisting Stair of Wrought Iron~
   This narrow spiral stair seems as though it would be quite frail when first
looked upon, with little in the way of materials or support.  However, setting
foot upon the first grated stair shows it to be quite stable, likely able to
support a great deal of weight despite its slender construction.  At the
heights near the ceiling the stairwell is plunged to darkness, while the vast
chamber below is lit with the flames of multiple sources.  While traversing the
heights of this chamber, the stair descends slightly to the south.    
